<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-625-567  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 625 567.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 9 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Big profit growth for Hong Kong Telecom.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wingrove, Norman.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hong Kong Telecommunications Ltd. (Earnings).andO;Topic:     Telecommunications ServicesTelephone CompaniesHong KongProfitGrowthFacsimileReports.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>BIG PROFIT GROWTH FOR HONG KONG TELECOM 11/09/90 WANCHAI, HONG KONG, 1990 NOV9 (NB) -- Hong Kong Telecom, the British colony's telecommunications giant,has announced profits for the half-year ended September of US$310,256,410million.andP;  This figure represents a rise of 17 percent and takes place againsta background of local uncertainty in the run-up to China's takeover of HongKong in July 1997, and of the continuing crisis in the Gulf.andM;The mainstay of what is widely regarded as an excellent mid-year result, is a19 percent increase in earnings from international traffic.andP;  A policy of lowmonthly rental charges and free local calls, coupled with inexpensiveinternational calls has for some time been the mainstay of the company'sprofits.andM;Another lucrative field of business continued to be facsimile services.andO;Although it is possible, as in other countries, for subscribers to connecttheir fax machines to ordinary voice lines, Telecom offers Faxline 100, aservice that guarantees a specially conditioned digital line with a range ofvalue-added services, including automatic remote checking of a user's system.andO;This results in almost 100 percent of local fax calls and a very highproportion of international calls connected at the maximum possibletransmission speed of 9600 bits per second.andM;In the past twelve months, Telecom achieved a Faxline 100 growth of 28percent.andM;(Norman Wingrove/19901107/Press Contact: HK Telecom, +852 808 6470; HK timeis GMT + 8)</TEXT></DOC>